Class UnsortedArrayIntSet

  • java.lang.Object
    • gov.nasa.jpf.util.ArrayIntSet
      • gov.nasa.jpf.util.UnsortedArrayIntSet
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    IntSet, Cloneable
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    TidSet

    public class UnsortedArrayIntSet
extends ArrayIntSet
    a simplistic IntSet implementation that uses an unsorted array to keep elements. Obviously this is O(N) and therefore not a good choice if the list grows, but if we know there are only a few elements then it isn't worth to do any sorting or fancy lookup - the JIT would beat algorithm. If the set is empty there is no memory allocated for the elements
